OL,6,FThe UK government has published the
OL,7,Fterms of reference for the independent
OL,8,Finquiry into the Omagh bomb.
OL,10,FTwenty-nine people, including a woman
OL,11,Fpregnant with twins, died after the
OL,12,Fdissident republican bomb exploded in
OL,13,Fthe Co Tyrone town on 15 August 1998.
OL,15,FThe terms of reference are focused on
OL,16,Fthe four grounds identified by the
OL,17,FNorthern Ireland High Court as giving
OL,18,Frise to plausible arguments that the
OL,19,Fbombing could have been prevented.
