OL,6,FThe inquiry will be established under
OL,7,Fthe Inquiries Act 2005, with full
OL,8,Fpowers, including the power to compel
OL,9,Fthe production of documents and to
OL,10,Fsummon witnesses to give evidence on
OL,11,Foath.
OL,13,F"With the Terms of Reference now
OL,14,Fagreed, the Inquiry can press ahead
OL,15,Fwith its work to comply with the
OL,16,Fjudgment of the High Court,
OL,17,Fdemonstrating the UK Government's
OL,18,Fongoing commitment to taking proper
OL,19,Faction on legacy related matters," Mr
OL,20,FHeaton-Harris continued.
