OL,6,FWhile having no jurisdiction to order
OL,7,Fthe Irish Government to act on the
OL,8,Fmatter, the judge urged authorities
OL,9,Fthere to establish their own probe in
OL,10,Flight of his findings.
OL,12,FOn Wednesday, Mr Heaton-Harris said:
OL,13,F"I urge the Irish Government to now
OL,14,Fexplain what consideration it has
OL,15,Fgiven to the setting up of an
OL,16,Finvestigation in Ireland to discharge
OL,17,Fits obligations under article 2 of the
OL,18,FEuropean Convention on Human Rights,
OL,19,Fin line with the clear direction of
OL,20,Fthe High Court."
